</taxonomicName>
is known from Madagascar from a single collection, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">Bosser 17019</emphasis>
(P [P00133154]!, TAN), from the Station 
<normalizedToken originalValue="d’Essais">d'Essais</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Caroline,”">&quot;Caroline,&quot;</normalizedToken>
Ilaka-Est [Toamasina Province, south of Vatomandry]. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schmelzer, GH" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" refId="B57" refString="Schmelzer, GH, 2007. Croton haumanianus J. Leonard. In: Schmelzer GH, Gurib-Fakim A (Eds) Prota 11(1): Medicinal plants/Plantes medicinales 1. [CD-Rom]. PROTA, Wageningen, Netherlands." title="Croton haumanianus J. Leonard. In: Schmelzer GH, Gurib-Fakim A (Eds) Prota 11 (1): Medicinal plants / Plantes medicinales 1. [CD-Rom]. PROTA, Wageningen, Netherlands." year="2007">Schmelzer (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. haumanianus" pageId="68" pageNumber="69" rank="species" species="haumanianus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="68" pageNumber="69">C. haumanianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly used as a shade plant in coffee and cacao plantations, which is likely the context of this report from Madagascar. No additional information is known as to whether this species has persisted in Madagascar.
</paragraph>
